      "side": 1,
      "message": "Consider a helper function:\n\n  func checkCanDoStuff(ctx context.Context) {\n     ...\n  }\n\nIt can be called in 3 scenarios:\n1. As a standalone check outside of any larger transactions: `checkCanDoStuff(span.Single(ctx))`.\n2. As a part of larger read-only transaction:\n   \n  ctx, cancel :\u003d span.ReadOnlyTransaction(ctx)\n  defer cancel()\n  ...\n  checkCanDoStuff(ctx)\n\n3. As a part of a read-write transaction:\n\n  span.ReadWriteTransaction(ctx, func(ctx context.Context) error {\n    checkCanDoStuff(ctx)\n    ...\n  })\n\nThe only way to support this is to consistently shove everything into context.Context. ResultDB has many instances of this pattern. It currently explicitly passes Txn object to such functions.",
